{"lemma":"ضَنْكٌ","slug":"ضَنْكٌ","root":"ض.ن.ك","root_slug":"ض-ن-ك","root_link":"/words/roots/ض-ن-ك","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ضَنْكٌ","root":"ضنك","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n26074"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B6%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%92%D9%83%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become weak, exhausted"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become straitened, exhausted, cramped, confined (of circumstances"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/dˤa.nu.ka/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n26074","headword_ar":"ضَنْكٌ","root":"Dnk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Danuka","text_ar":"ضَنُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, K:) its primary signification is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Narrowness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"straitness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hardship."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Is-hák, TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Narrow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strait;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Day~iqN","text_ar":"ضَيِّقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, O, K; [in the CK, and in a copy of the S,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Diyq","text_ar":"ضِيق"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is also a correct explanation, as shown above; but not what is here meant, as appears from what follows;]) applied to anything, (M, K,) masc."},{"kind":"page_break","n":1807},{"kind":"text","text":"and fem., (M, K, and Bd in xx. 123,) being an inf. n. used as an epithet. (Bd ibid.) [Like the Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanoG","text_ar":"تَنْگ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] One says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makaAnN DanokN","text_ar":"مَكَانٌ ضَنْكٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A narrow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strait, place."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, O, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eayo$N DanokN","text_ar":"عَيْشٌ ضَنْكٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A strait life;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strait sustenance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"means of subsistence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, O, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eayo$N DaniykN","text_ar":"عَيْشٌ ضَنِيكٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AA, O, K, TA:) and thus"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEiy$apF DanokFA","text_ar":"مَعِيشَةً ضَنْكًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur xx. 123; where some read ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DanokaY","text_ar":"ضَنْكَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakoraY","text_ar":"سَكْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Bd:) or this means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is unlawful;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA;) every life that is unlawful being termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DanokN","text_ar":"ضَنْكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to Lth, even though it be ample: (O, TA: *) Aboo-Is-hák thinks it to mean ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"subsistence"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the fire of Hell:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but says that most explain this phrase in the Kur as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the punishment of the grave:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) thus it means accord. to Ibn-Mes'ood: (O:) or, accord. to Katádeh,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hell:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA:) or, accord. to Ed-Dahhák,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forbidden gain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~ariyEu","text_ar":"الضَّرِيعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alz~ak~uwmu","text_ar":"الزَّكُّومُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (Bd.)"}],"source_refs":["O","K","M","AA","TA","Bd"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}